COPYLEFT (c) Aleš Kuklínek

Copyleft is a licensing method that ensures software or other creative works remain free and open for use, modification, and redistribution. Under a copyleft license, anyone can use, modify, and distribute the work, but any derivative works must also be distributed under the same or a compatible license. This ensures that the freedoms granted by the original creator are preserved and passed on to future users and developers. Examples of copyleft licenses include the GNU General Public License (GPL) and Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike (CC BY-SA).
